The paper discusses an experimental study on the performance of the K-means algorithm with different distance measures on clustering the iris and wine datasets. This study falls under the category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) as it deals with clustering algorithms. Additionally, the use of different distance measures indicates the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also involves data analysis and pattern recognition, which are the key components of data mining (cs.DM). The iris dataset is a popular dataset used in computer vision (cs.CV) for classification tasks, and the wine dataset is used in natural language processing (cs.CL) for sentiment analysis. Therefore, these categories are also likely to be relevant to this paper.
